Queue Advanced Topic and Understanding

10-03-2024


Add is used to insert a specified element into the queue. It returns true when the task is successful or else it throws an exception. 
Offer is used to insert a specified element into the queue. It returns true when the task is successful or else its return false.

import java.util.*;
public class Kushagra {
 
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        Queue<String> pq = new PriorityQueue<>();
        pq.add("Geeks");
        pq.add("For");
        pq.add("Geeks");
        System.out.println(pq); // print queue
        pq.remove("Geeks"); // remove an item in O(1) time
        System.out.println(pq.poll()); // return first element of the queue
        pq.isEmpty(); // return true if queue is empty otherwise false
        pq.size(); // pq size return
        System.out.println(pq);
    }
}

Insted of add we can also write offer.

